President Biden hosted a videoconference with Allies and partners to discuss international support for Ukraine in response to Russian aggression. They affirmed solidarity with the Ukrainian people and condemned Russia's invasion. They also discussed efforts to impose economic costs on Russia and committed to close consultation with the G7, EU, and NATO. The leaders in attendance included Prime Minister Trudeau of Canada, President von der Leyen and President Michel of the European Commission and Council, President Macron of France, Chancellor Scholz of Germany, Prime Minister Draghi of Italy, Prime Minister Kishida of Japan, NATO Secretary General Stoltenberg, President Duda of Poland, President Iohannis of Romania, and Prime Minister Johnson of the United Kingdom.